# GolferGeek AI Dev Curriculum (Cursor + Claude Code)

## Two tools, one playbook

- **Claude Code** (CLI / subscription): **Slash commands** live in **`.claude/commands/`** — `/intention`, `/prd`, `/plan`, `/run-plan`. Skills and agents are under **`.claude/skills/`** and **`.claude/agents/`**. That is the **authoritative** automation path for Phase 00.
- **Cursor** (this IDE): There is **no** native `/run-plan` in Cursor that invokes those files. Cursor **reads** this rule plus project files. Follow the **same sequence** using [docs/phase-00/RUN-ORDER.md](../../docs/phase-00/RUN-ORDER.md) and the same artifacts under **`docs/artifacts/`**.

## What to do in Cursor

1. Open [docs/phase-00/STARTER-KIT.md](../../docs/phase-00/STARTER-KIT.md) and [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md).
2. Execute the workflow **in order** (intention → PRD → plan → implement or delegate). Treat **`.claude/commands/*.md`** as **prompt templates**: read the file and perform that role in chat if not using Claude Code slash commands.
3. When editing code, respect [docs/phase-00/intention-monorepo.md](../../docs/phase-00/intention-monorepo.md) once the monorepo exists; use skills **monorepo-turbo** and **prd-alignment** by reading **`.claude/skills/`** and applying that discipline.
4. Prefer **@** references to `docs/phase-00/` and `.claude/` so context stays aligned with the course.

## Not automatic cross-calls

Cursor does **not** “call” Claude Code skills remotely. This rule **mirrors intent** so both tools stay consistent. For **verified** slash-command behavior, use **Claude Code** in this repo.
